<br>
Hades needed to be taught that even Gods have performed events they become not proud of, certainly the God of the Underworld knew this!<br>
<br>
Gaia sat quietly, Hades was indeed her grandson but the rift had made Gaia nothing to Hades. Gaia would merely sit quietly through this. She would not cause an uproar during a trial and disrespect Athena, and the Erinyes positions as Servers of Justice.<br>
<br>
Her emerald hues glanced around the room at everyone who had attended before her orbs turned back to Poseidon and Hades.<br>
<br>
She was Mother Earth, Mother of the Titans and the First of the Gods. If had not been for her existence, Hades nor anyone else would be here. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hypnos>Hypnos </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.backtalk.org/shadowydreamer/anime/zagato1.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 312<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/22/02 9:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reading minds</span><hr size=1> ***probably no noe in the room knew that Hypnos could listen to there thoughts as they thought them, but he did hear them.*** <br>
 <br>
&quot;Don't let you pride cover you Gaia, I don't have to give you any thankfulness for being hear for my mother was your sister.&quot; <br>
 <br>
***Hypnos got up and went over to stand next to Hades. He would have gone through this trial but the the gods judging him were going a little too far, for some of them had no reason to be there. <br>
 <br>
Now that he knew that Hades was giving him some support, he could stand up for himself now.***   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/23/02 12:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/gaia12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> erm, No.</span><hr size=1> ((OK, that wasnt an actual thought.So when he &quot;read&quot; her mind not much was read. and so that response is blocked.))<br>
<br>
Gaia sat there. She knew it, this was inevitable. The Gods bickering, it was like posion to her ears. She coudln't stand the ignorance that had materialized here.<br>
<br>
Poseidon, Athena, Hades, Hypnos all of them became oblivious to her. She closed her eyes and disappeared from the scene. Leaving only soil and where she once sat. <p>~*-:¦:-*~Gaia: Greek Goddess of Earth~*-:¦:-*~ <BR>-§Mother Earth§-¤Mother of the Titans¤-¥Mother of All Creation¥-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/24/02 4:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Justice be Done</span><hr size=1> Athena listened to everything spoken and she looked to Gaia as she vanished from their sight. She sighed lightly and stood.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then it is decided by myself as well as the obvious choices of the rally of Olympians.&quot;<br>
<br>
She stood and looked to the Erinyes as they too stood and awaited her &quot;sentancing&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your defense for him has been considered Hades, and because of such, I have decided a proper punishment. The Underworld is where you claim him to reside, and it will be the Underworld he shall remain. Keeping the mortals with their proper sleep, and not to abuse his powers.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked to Alecto and nodded.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are the only Furie allowed into Tartarus without Hades' permission, should he leave the Underworld and continue this mischief, you are to track him down and bring him forth again for a more tormentful punishment.&quot;<br>
<br>
She sat back down on her thrown a bit appalled at how her &quot;Family&quot; reacted to eachother in this situation. How she hated having to be the serious one.<br>
<br>
&quot;Justice be served.&quot;<br>
<br>
And with that, she vanished. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 186<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/26/02 5:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...And Justice For All</span><hr size=1> ::Hades stood still as his brother, Poseidon, spoke to him.  He listened very quietly as he spoke, nodding slightly::<br>
<br>
::Hades then shifted his attention to the seat that his 'grandmother' Gaia once occupied.  He smirked as he knew she was very uncomfortable around him.  This amused him greatly.::<br>
<br>
::He then turned his attention to Athena who was now passing judgement.  He simply nodded and walked up to her. He whispered in her ear, though the other Olympians in the room could very audibly hear him::<br>
<br>
&quot;You show great Wisdom, dear Athena.  Even greater Wisdom than your Father.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He backs off from her and stands in the middle of the room:: &quot;I do however, request to make one ammendment to that.  Hypnos be allowed to come to the surface in the company of one of the 'responsible' gods.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/28/02 6:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Punishment</span><hr size=1> Alecto nodded to Athena and took a gaze at Hades.<br>
Megaera and Tisiphone giggled lightly amongst themselves.<br>
<br>
Alecto then stepped forward.<br>
<br>
&quot;He may. However, that Responsible one shall be decided by myself or a higher. In a way I too am responsible for him Hades. You keep the Immortal under watch, if not . . . he's mine.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera stepped forward.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take him to Tartarus Hades.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alecto spoke.<br>
&quot;And remember, we'll be watching.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that the Furies vanished in open flames. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 325<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/28/02 6:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Punishment</span><hr size=1> Poseidon was pleased with all things that had taken place and now that the trial was over he was readying to leave. Before he left he waved to his brother and laughed at the Erinyes. Then the god of the sea vanished from the open area. His chair remained there and he left everyone else to their own doings. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.cybercomm.net/~grandpa/euterpe.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/30/02 1:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=260.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jonathonart.com/LotusMaiden1/dark1s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> HEKATE'S EXIT</span><hr size=1> As Hades appears she smirks<br>
